headline: C.H. Robinson Q4 Earnings Surpass Estimates, Increase Year Over Year
summary: CHRW's Q4 revenues are hurt by the divestiture of its Europe Surface Transportation business, lower pricing and volume in the ocean services and lower pricing in the truckload services.

headline: CHRW Q4 Deep Dive: Market Share Gains and Lean AI Strategy Offset Freight Headwinds
summary: Freight transportation intermediary C.H. Robinson (NASDAQ:CHRW) fell short of the markets revenue expectations in Q4 CY2025, with sales falling 6.5% year on year to $3.91 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $1.23 per share was 9.2% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
